+- **Blob volume = named volume + one-shot `blob-init` mounter.**
+  Empirical Compose behavior verified during planning: a
+  top-level `volumes:` declaration **does not** cause Compose to
+  create the volume unless at least one service mounts it. A
+  bare declaration (no mount, no init service) leaves
+  `docker volume ls` empty after `compose up`. To make 10a's
+  deliverable real, we ship a one-shot `blob-init` busybox
+  container that mounts `eden-blob-data` at `/var/lib/eden/blobs`,
+  runs `mkdir -p` + a permission-set, and exits 0. `restart: "no"`
+  prevents the exited container from looping; `docker compose up
+  --wait` semantics for one-shot services were also verified
+  during planning — `--wait` returns exit 0 when a one-shot
+  container exits 0, so the smoke test gets a clean signal.
+  Downstream services in 10b/10d mount the same volume.
+  10a's smoke test asserts via `docker volume inspect
+  eden-reference_eden-blob-data` *and* re-runs a busybox container
+  against the volume to confirm it's writable.
